      • hasNext

        boolean hasNext()
        Indicates whether the search has a next page or not. This method can return true if there is a limit parameter set in the Search criteria and backend can return more results than the limit. It should return false if this result if the last page of the search result, backend doesn't have more contacts than the limit, or limit is not set at all.
        Returns:
        true if search has a next page

      • getNext

        void getNext(SearchCallback callback)
        Retrieves the next page of the results.
        Parameters:
        callback - SearchCallback that handles success and error situations of the operation.
